  "local_port": 36916,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best Bank robbery movies?",
  "response": "Here is a list of some of the best bank robbery movies, known for their thrilling plots, strong performances, and memorable heists:\n\n1. **Heat (1995)**\n   - Directed by Michael Mann, this film follows a group of professional bank robbers led by Neil McCauley (Robert De Niro) as they plan a heist, while being pursued by a dedicated detective, Vincent Hanna (Al Pacino).\n\n2. **Dog Day Afternoon (1975)**\n   - Directed by Sidney Lumet and starring Al Pacino, this film is based on a true story of a bank robbery gone wrong. Pacino plays Sonny Wortzik, who attempts to rob a bank to pay for his lover's sex reassignment surgery.\n\n3. **The Bank Job (2008)**\n   - Directed by Roger Donaldson, this film is inspired by the 1971 Baker Street robbery in London. Jason Statham stars as Terry Leather, who leads a team in a seemingly straightforward heist that uncovers much more than they bargained for.\n\n4. **Point Break (1991)**\n   - Directed by Kathryn Bigelow, this action thriller follows an FBI agent, Johnny Utah (Keanu Reeves), who goes undercover to infiltrate a gang of bank robbers led by the charismatic Bodhi (Patrick Swayze).\n\n5. **The Town (2010)**\n   - Directed by and starring Ben Affleck, this film is based on the novel \"Prince of Thieves\" by Chuck Hogan. It follows a group of bank robbers in Charlestown, Boston, as they plan their next heist while the FBI closes in.\n\n6. **Inside Man (2006)**\n   - Directed by Spike Lee, this intelligent thriller stars Denzel Washington as a NYPD hostage negotiator trying to resolve a bank heist led by the cunning Dalton Russell (Clive Owen).\n\n7. **Hell or High Water (2016)**\n   - Directed by David Mackenzie, this modern western crime thriller follows two brothers, Toby (Chris Pine) and Tanner Howard (Ben Foster), who rob banks to save their family ranch, while being pursued by a Texas Ranger (Jeff Bridges).\n\n8. **The Killing (1956)**\n   - Directed by Stanley Kubrick, this classic noir film follows a group of criminals led by Johnny Clay (Sterling Hayden) as they plan an elaborate racetrack heist. Though not a traditional bank robbery, it shares many themes and elements.\n\n9. **Reservoir Dogs (1992)**\n   - Directed by Quentin Tarantino, this film focuses on the aftermath of a failed diamond heist. Though the heist itself is not shown, the film's intense dialogue and character dynamics have made it a cult classic.\n\n10. **The Italian Job (1969)**\n    - Directed by Peter Collinson, this classic film follows a team of thieves led by Charlie Croker (Michael Caine) as they plan an audacious gold heist in Turin, Italy. The film is known for its iconic Mini Cooper chase scenes.\n\nThese movies are celebrated for their suspense, intricate plots, and unforgettable characters, making them some of the best in the genre.",
